==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Awabakal]] language ''[[gurri]]'', as spoken in the area of what is today Newcastle, adopted by indigenous people of other areas.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-es}}
# An Australian [[aborigine]].

====Usage notes====
This term is preferred by the indigenous people of [[Victoria]] and most of [[New South Wales]], expressing pride in their heritage and race. (The peoples of other areas have other preferred terms.) (Reference: [[w:R. M. W. Dixon|R. M. W. Dixon]], Australian Aboriginal Words'', Oxford University Press, 1990, ISBN 0-19-553099-3, pages 169 and 221.)

